{"type":"user.message","data":{"content":"I'm starting a new .NET MAUI project on .NET 10. I found a tutorial that says\nto add `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` to my ContentPage to handle the iPhone\nnotch. Is this the right approach? Also, the tutorial mentions using\n`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid for a background image. Are these correct\nfor .NET 10?\n","transformedContent":"<current_datetime>2026-05-16T00:54:04.146Z</current_datetime>\n\nI'm starting a new .NET MAUI project on .NET 10. I found a tutorial that says\nto add `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` to my ContentPage to handle the iPhone\nnotch. Is this the right approach? Also, the tutorial mentions using\n`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid for a background image. Are these correct\nfor .NET 10?","attachments":[],"interactionId":"d6dce523-f005-4ac8-ae10-4eebb7914529"},"id":"787213a6-567c-4287-9271-38c88d1465d4","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:54:04.146Z","parentId":"8e0dfd67-9431-4e73-8825-e50b0557b09e"}
