{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6b4d95f3-e6d4-42d9-bc15-9511b6e68971","content":"Yes, both approaches are correct for .NET MAUI on .NET 10.\n\n**`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — This is the iOS platform-specific that insets your page content to avoid the notch/Dynamic Island. Add the namespace:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage\n    xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n    ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\">\n```\n\nOr in code-behind:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration;\nusing Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;\n\nOn<iOS>().SetUseSafeArea(true);\n```\n\n**`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"`** — This lets a specific layout (like a Grid holding a background image) extend into the unsafe areas, even when the page uses safe area. This is the standard pattern for edge-to-edge backgrounds:\n\n```xml\n<Grid IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\">\n    <Image Source=\"background.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n</Grid>\n```\n\nBoth APIs are stable and remain the recommended approach in .NET 10 MAUI. Your tutorial is correct.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d6dce523-f005-4ac8-ae10-4eebb7914529","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI safe area handling on iOS, specifically about two properties:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - a platform-specific property for ContentPage\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` - a property on Grid for background images\n\nLet me check what I know about these APIs in .NET MAUI, particularly for .NET 10.\n\nIn .NET MAUI (which evolved from Xamarin.Forms), the safe area handling changed:\n\n1. **`ios:Page.UseSafeArea`** - This was a Xamarin.Forms iOS platform-specific. In .NET MAUI, this was initially carried over but the API surface has evolved. \n\nIn .NET MAUI, safe area insets are handled through the `IgnoreSafeArea` property available on layouts, which allows content to extend into safe area regions. The `Page.UseSafeArea` platform-specific from Xamarin.Forms uses the iOS namespace `clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls`, and `IgnoreSafeArea` is a property on views that controls whether they respect safe area boundaries. Both of these are valid .NET MAUI APIs that should still work in .NET 10, so the tutorial approach is sound. I'll confirm these are the correct methods and provide context on when to use each one.","outputTokens":977,"requestId":"D449:28D4C6:1BABA7B:1F32D54:6A07C02C"},"id":"d1d7d05b-35ef-4ae5-8359-f53d738fd4e9","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:54:21.937Z","parentId":"bd6e1612-3554-4a9e-b57c-0ba69f820242"}
